    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "@Haroenv I have another interesting finding. The issue also happens in `stateResults` provided by `connectStateResults` but only if `connectStateResults` is _after_ the hits. See here on the following screenshots, `connectStateResults` does not provide the same values when before/after the hits:\r\n\r\n<img width=\"601\" alt=\"image\" src=\"https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/7127784/166470534-c9e6aa47-bac7-4c1d-9d41-c395b3f5be8f.png\">\r\n\r\n<img width=\"599\" alt=\"image\" src=\"https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/7127784/166470737-41ff0821-31ca-46c4-baa2-71ea0d02c8f3.png\">\r\n\r\nI remember there was an issue depending on the order of the components [here](https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch.js/issues/5255) as well. Maybe this will give you a lead?\r\n",
